attributes.additional_details:
Labour's attack on pensioners and farmers, lack of action to tackle uncontrolled migration, surrender of Sovereignty of the Chagos Islands costing UK tax payers billions & the recent "deal" with the EU resulting in a backwards step in UK fishing rights & immigration control is unforgivable.

The Labour Government are not acting in accordance with the desires or best interests of British Citizens, and we want an immediate general election to prevent any further damage to the UK.
attributes.background: Keir Starmer and the Labour Government have gone too far and are not acting in the best interests or wants of the Great British public. We want the Prime Minister to call for an immediate general election by calling a dissolution of Parliament from the Sovereign.

rejection.details:
You may wish to sign the following petition, which calls for similar action:
